This paper deals with a computational approach for computing common generalizations of ground terms w.r.t. a given equational background theory. This problem is related to logic and automated reasoning, which falls under the category of cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also mentions a Prolog prototype implementation, which suggests that it may be related to programming languages and compilers, falling under the category of cs.PL (Programming Languages). Additionally, the paper discusses algorithmic improvements and efficiency-oriented implementation, which are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures (cs.DS), and software engineering (cs.SE).
